      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — non-cannulated",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared to N=11 experimental measurements. Mean absolute error 4.2%; E/uval = 0.87 (< 1.96 acceptance threshold). The accompanying UQ campaign varied elastic modulus, friction coefficient, and screw-rod interface contact stiffness across their uncertainty ranges; sensitivity indices (Sobol first-order) confirmed elastic modulus as the dominant driver, accounting for 68% of output variance. These findings informed the final acceptance bounds and are documented in the UQ campaign report (internal ref: UQR-2023-NC-01).",
      "outcomeValue": "4.2% mean absolute error; E/uval = 0.87",
